---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import BlueskyProfileCard from "../components/BlueskyProfileCard.astro";
import GitHubProfileCard from "../components/GitHubProfileCard.astro";
import Icon from "../components/Icon.astro";
import talksData from "../../content/talks/talks.json";
const talks = [...talksData.talks].sort((a, b) => b.date.localeCompare(a.date));
---

<BaseLayout
    title="About — Software Security"
    description="Andrew Lilley Brinker is a Principal Engineer at MITRE working on software security, vulnerability information, and open source tooling."
    socialImage="/social/about.png"
    socialImageAlt="About — Software Security"
>
    <h1>About</h1>
    <div
        class="inline-block relative group max-w-36 md:max-w-48 transition-all duration-300 rotate-3 hover:rotate-0 float-right ml-4 md:ml-8 mb-4 md:mb-8 -top-10"
    >
        <img
            src="/image/andrew.png"
            alt="Grayscale and dithered picture of Andrew"
            width="500"
            height="500"
            loading="eager"
            class="rounded-md block group-hover:ring-4 group-hover:ring-blue-500 transition-all duration-300"
        />
    </div>
    <p>
        I’m a Principal Engineer at <a href="https://www.mitre.org">MITRE</a>
        &nbsp;working on software security, vulnerability management, and open source.
        I lead <a href="https://github.com/mitre/hipcheck">Hipcheck</a>, which
        helps maintainers and users assess dependency supply-chain risk via
        plugin-based analyses.
    </p>
    <p>
        I also work on the <a href="https://www.cve.org/">CVE</a> system, improving
        authz&ThinSpace;/&ThinSpace;authn, introducing support for <a
            href="https://packageurl.org/">Package URLs</a
        > in CVE Records, and enhancing the processes of the Quality Working Group.
    </p>
    <p>
        I previously served on the <a href="https://omnibor.io/">OmniBOR</a> Core
        Team, including leading creation of the <a
            href="https://github.com/omnibor/omnibor-rs"
            >Rust library and omnibor CLI</a
        >.
    </p>
    <aside class="rounded-lg bg-white px-5 py-4 shadow-sm dark:bg-neutral-800">
        <h2 id="my-name" class="!mt-0 !mb-3 !font-sans !text-sm !font-semibold">
            My Name
        </h2>
        <p class="!m-0 !text-sm">
            “Lilley Brinker” is my full last name. Two parts, no hyphen. When my
            wife and I got married we combined our last names without a hyphen.
            My last name is not “Brinker” and it is not correct to call me “Mr.
            Brinker”.
        </p>
        <p class="!mt-2 !mb-0 !text-sm">
            “Lilley” is pronounced like the word “lily”.
        </p>
    </aside>
    <h2 class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4">
        <span>Work</span><a
            href="/resume.pdf"
            class="group inline-flex shrink-0 items-center gap-2 rounded-md border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2 font-sans text-sm font-medium leading-none !no-underline hover:bg-blue-100 dark:border-neutral-700 dark:hover:bg-neutral-800"
            >Résumé <span
                class="rounded-sm bg-neutral-100 px-1 py-0.5 text-[0.625rem] font-semibold tracking-wide group-hover:bg-neutral-200 dark:bg-neutral-700 dark:group-hover:bg-neutral-600"
                >PDF</span
            ></a
        >
    </h2>
    <p>
        I want the people who build and maintain software to be able to make
        informed decisions about what they depend on. That is why I founded <a
            href="https://github.com/mitre/hipcheck">Hipcheck</a
        > and led its redesign as an extensible supply-chain analysis tool.
    </p>
    <p>
        I am drawn to work at the intersection of technical standards, public
        policy, and open source communities. I have advised federal software
        policy on SBOMs and open source security, and through <a
            href="https://omnibor.io">OmniBOR</a
        >, I worked on better ways to handle software identity.
    </p>
    <p>
        Memory safety matters to me because it makes software safer by default.
        In <a href="https://queue.acm.org/detail.cfm?id=3773095"
            >“Memory Safety for Skeptics”</a
        >, published in <em>ACM Queue</em> and <em>Communications of the ACM</em>,
        I make the case for pursuing it amid competing priorities. I have taught
        Rust at MITRE and programming language theory at <a
            href="https://cse.csusb.edu">CSUSB</a
        >, spoken at <a
            href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0PhfaFkzdBA">RustConf</a
        > and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Wz2oFEDwiOk"
            >Rust Belt Rust</a
        >, contributed to the official Rust documentation and Rustonomicon, and
        edited <a
            href="https://www.manning.com/books/write-powerful-rust-macros"
            >a book on Rust procedural macros</a
        >.
    </p>
    <h3
        id="talks"
        class="!font-sans !text-lg !font-normal !tracking-normal text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400"
    >
        Talks
    </h3>
    {
        talks.map((talk) => (
            <article class="mb-10">
                <h4 class="!m-0 !mb-1 !font-display !text-xl !font-medium">
                    <a
                        class="text-black dark:text-white no-underline hover:underline"
                        href={talk.talk_link}
                    >
                        {talk.title}
                    </a>
                </h4>
                <div class="flex gap-4 flex-wrap text-sm text-gray-500">
                    <span>
                        {talk.type === "panel"
                            ? "Participated in panel at"
                            : "Presented at"}{" "}
                        <a href={talk.event_link}>{talk.event}</a> on{" "}
                        {new Date(`${talk.date}T12:00:00Z`).toLocaleDateString(
                            "en-US",
                            {
                                month: "long",
                                day: "numeric",
                                year: "numeric",
                                timeZone: "UTC",
                            },
                        )}
                    </span>
                    {talk.video_link && (
                        <span>
                            <a href={talk.video_link}>Watch the Recording</a>
                        </span>
                    )}
                    {talk.slides_link && (
                        <span>
                            <a href={talk.slides_link}>View the Slides</a>
                        </span>
                    )}
                </div>
                {talk.description && <p class="!mt-2">{talk.description}</p>}
            </article>
        ))
    }
    <h2 id="where-to-find-me">Social / Contact</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
        <BlueskyProfileCard />
        <GitHubProfileCard />
    </div>
    <p class="!mb-2">Message me on Bluesky for my Signal username to chat.</p>
    <p
        class="!mt-2 !text-sm !leading-relaxed text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400 [&_a]:!text-neutral-500 dark:[&_a]:!text-neutral-400"
    >
        You can also find me on <a href="https://hachyderm.io/@alilleybrinker"
            >Mastodon</a
        >, <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alilleybrinker">LinkedIn</a>, <a
            href="https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=alilleybrinker"
            >Hacker News</a
        >, <a href="https://lobste.rs/~alilleybrinker">Lobste.rs</a>, and <a
            href="https://www.reddit.com/user/alilleybrinker/">Reddit</a
        >.
    </p>
    <h2 id="ai-policy">AI Policy</h2>
    <p>
        The words on this site were written by Andrew with care. Its design was
        implemented with the aid of AI. If AI-generated content is ever posted,
        it will be clearly identified.
    </p>
</BaseLayout>
